Published operator guidance in the public MDX docs:
- `website/docs/start-here/capabilities.mdx`
- `website/docs/start-here/server-first-run.mdx`
- `website/docs/concepts/embedded-and-server.mdx`

Guidance added:
- retention is explicit per stream and defaults to `none`
- retention trims whole rolled segments only
- retention is not Kafka-style compaction
- retention is not selective erasure

Observed result:
- the public docs now distinguish retention clearly from compaction and privacy erasure
